:[{"name":"Cranfield","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Bedfordshire named Cranfield, from Old English <i>cran(uc)</i> ‘crane’ + <i>feld</i> ‘open country’."],"variants":[{"name":"Cranfill","meanings":["English: probably a local (Cambridgeshire) variant of   Cranfield  . It is apparently no longer found in Britain. In the US, it is found mainly in NC, TX, and IN."]},{"name":"Cornfield","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   Cranfield  .","Americanized form (translation into English) of Jewish or German   Kornfeld  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Glover","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern coinage taken from the word denoting the plant (Old English <i>clāfre</i>)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Glover Cranfield Sr. was born in 1483, in Barford, Bedfordshire, England, his father, William Glover, was 40 and his mother, Joan Glover, was 44. He married Katherine Dale Odell in 1512, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1533, in his hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1483–1533":"1483–1533","1487–1565":"1487–1565","1514–1570":"1514–1570","1525–1614":"1525–1614","1443–1489":"1443–1489","1439–1554":"1439–1554","6 June 1489":"6. juuni 1489","1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1525":"1525","1514":"1514","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1489":"1489","1 January 1514":"1. jaanuar 1514","about 1525":"umbes 1525","1554":"1554","1565":"1565","1443":"1443","1487":"1487","1439":"1439","1614":"1614","Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barford, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barford, Kempston Parish, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1483–1533":"1483–1533","1487–1565":"1487–1565","1514–1570":"1514–1570","1525–1614":"1525–1614","1443–1489":"1443–1489","1439–1554":"1439–1554","6 June 1489":"6. kesäkuuta 1489","1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1525":"1525","1514":"1514","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1489":"1489","1 January 1514":"1. tammikuuta 1514","about 1525":"noin 1525","1554":"1554","1565":"1565","1443":"1443","1487":"1487","1439":"1439","1614":"1614","Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barford, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barford, Kempston Parish, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1483–1533":"1483–1533","1487–1565":"1487–1565","1514–1570":"1514–1570","1525–1614":"1525–1614","1443–1489":"1443–1489","1439–1554":"1439–1554","6 June 1489":"6 juin 1489","1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1525":"1525","1514":"1514","1512":"1512","1533